annually. He is passionate about console preservation and hardware firmware modifications.\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"space-y-1.5 border-t border-border/60 pt-3\",\"children\":[[[\"$\",\"span\",\"QA Lead Certified\",{\"className\":\"block text-[8px] text-foreground-muted\",\"children\":[\"🏅 \",\"QA Lead Certified\"]}]],[\"$\",\"a\",null,{\"href\":\"mailto:alex.mercer@gamepadtester.live\",\"className\":\"block text-[9px] text-accent hover:underline mt-1\",\"children\":[\"✉️ \",\"alex.mercer@gamepadtester.live\"]}]]}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"bg-surface border border-border rounded-xl p-5 shadow-sm\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"text-[10px] font-bold font-display text-success uppercase tracking-widest block mb-3\",\"children\":\"Technical Reviewer\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"img\",null,{\"src\":\"/sarah-chen.jpg\",\"alt\":\"Sarah Chen, PhD portrait\",\"className\":\"w-10 h-10 rounded-full object-cover border border-border\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L3\",null,{\"href\":\"/author/sarah-chen\",\"className\":\"text-xs font-bold text-foreground hover:text-primary transition leading-tight block\",\"children\":\"Sarah Chen, PhD\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"text-[9px] text-foreground-muted\",\"children\":\"Senior Hardware Systems Consultant\"}]]}]]}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-[10px] text-foreground-secondary leading-relaxed mb-3\",\"children\":\"Sarah is an electrical engineer and input device specialist. She consults on signal latency testing, firmware analysis, and cross-platform Gamepad API calibration protocols. Her academic research focuses on micro-contact potentiometer noise signals and mitigation patterns.\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"space-y-1.5 border-t border-border/60 pt-3\",\"children\":[[[\"$\",\"span\",\"Ph.D. in Electrical Engineering\",{\"className\":\"block text-[8px] text-foregrou